<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911203-0132</DOCNO><DOCID>911203-0132.</DOCID><HL>   Macy Makes Deferred Payment</HL><DATE>12/03/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C16</SO><CO>   MZ</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)BROADLINE RETAILERS, DEPARTMENT STORES (RTB)</IN><NS>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   NEW YORK -- R.H. Macy andamp; Co. made a $48 million interestpayment to Prudential Insurance Co. of America that wasoriginally due Nov. 1 but was deferred by both parties untilyesterday.   Macy's debt repayment plans have been closely watched inthe junk bond market. Macy, one of the largest U.S.retailers, has sizable debts that were taken on when thecompany went private in a leveraged buy-out in 1986.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>